In Continuous Deliverythe authors talk about the danger of ultimate configurability&hellip;
&hellip;and from my experience when you take this over configurability to its logical conclusion you end up developing a framework that can hopefully just be &lsquo;configured&rsquo; for any number of &lsquo;front ends&rsquo;.
